1. Initializations

% Clear all variables, close all figures, and clear the command window
clearvars
close all
clc
% Display the matrices with rectangular brackets
sympref('MatrixWithSquareBrackets',true);
% Turn off abbreviated output format (avoid Matlab's own substitution of long expressions)
sympref('AbbreviateOutput',false);
% Symbolic variables to be used (see the figures and explanations below)
syms x y % Absolute coords of the pivot joint
syms x_dot y_dot % Absolute velocity components of the pivot joint
syms alpha % Absolute angle of the platform
syms alpha_dot % Absolute angular velocity of the platform
syms varphi_r % Angle of right wheel
syms varphi_l % Angle of left wheel
syms varphi_p % Relative angle at the pivot joint (platform wrt base)
syms varphi_dot_l % Angular velocity of left wheel
syms varphi_dot_r % Angular velocity of right wheel
syms varphi_dot_p % Angular velocity of the platform relative to the chassis body
syms l_1 % Pivot offset relative to the wheels axis
syms l_2 % One half of the wheels separation
syms m_b m_w m_p % Masses of the chassis base, one wheel, and the platform
syms x_G y_G % Coords of the c.o.m. of the chassis body in the chassis frame
syms x_F y_F % Coords of the c.o.m. of the platform body in the platform frame
syms I_b % Central moment of inertia of the chassis body about axis 3
syms I_p % Central moment of inertia of the platform body about axis 3"
syms I_a % Axial moment of inertia of one wheel
syms I_t % Twisting moment of inertia of one wheel
% Load matrices
load('Mmatrix.mat')
load('Cmatrix.mat')
load('forward_inverse_jacobians.mat')

2. Equation of motion in task-space coordinates

Our goal is to obtain an equation of motion that describes the time evolution of the coordinates alone, and at the same time does not contain the annoying Lagrange multipliers . In this way we will obtain a one-to-one relationship between platform accelerations and the torques of the robot. This relationship can later be used to design a computed-torque control law.
